  "text": "TLS Configuration Architecture Across the Prometheus Stack\n\nThe Prometheus monitoring stack enforces TLS configuration across all external-facing interfaces through a unified architecture centered on the TLSConfig struct defined in the prometheus-common library.\n\n## TLS Struct Definition (Canonical)\nThe canonical TLSConfig struct is defined in `sourcegraph-testing/prometheus-common/config/http_config.go` and includes: CAFile, CertFile, KeyFile, ServerName, and InsecureSkipVerify. The NewTLSConfig factory function converts this configuration into a standard Go tls.Config with proper certificate loading, CA chain validation, and client certificate handling via LoadX509KeyPair and AppendCertsFromPEM.\n\n## Configuration Embedding\nTLSConfig is embedded within HTTPClientConfig and wired into all major Prometheus configuration types:\n- ScrapeConfig (config/config.go): Enables TLS for scraping targets via embedded HTTPClientConfig\n- RemoteWriteConfig (config/config.go): Enables TLS for remote write endpoints via embedded HTTPClientConfig\n- RemoteReadConfig (config/config.go): Enables TLS for remote read endpoints via embedded HTTPClientConfig\n- AlertmanagerConfig (config/config.go): Enables TLS for alertmanager communication via embedded HTTPClientConfig\n- TracingConfig (config/config.go): Contains direct TLSConfig field for OTLP tracing exporters\n\n## Client-Side TLS Application\nThe prometheus/prometheus codebase applies TLS configuration at multiple layers:\n- scrape/scrape.go:145: Uses config_util.NewClientFromConfig to create HTTP clients with TLS for target scraping\n- storage/remote/client.go:159,188: Applies HTTPClientConfig with TLS for remote storage read/write clients\n- storage/remote/write.go:177: Uses HTTPClientConfig with TLS for remote write endpoint communication\n- storage/remote/storage.go:123: Uses HTTPClientConfig with TLS for remote read endpoint communication\n- tracing/tracing.go:189,222: Applies NewTLSConfig to both gRPC (credentials.NewTLS) and HTTP OTLP exporters\n\n## Server-Side TLS Setup\nThe web server TLS is configured via:\n- web/web.go:709: Invokes toolkit_web.ServeMultiple with webConfig parameter for server-side TLS\n- cmd/prometheus/main.go:1337: Passes webConfig file to enable web server TLS via exporter-toolkit\n\n## Service Discovery Plugin TLS Support\nService discovery plugins universally implement TLS support through embedded HTTPClientConfig or dedicated TLSConfig fields:\n- discovery/kubernetes/kubernetes.go:112: HTTPClientConfig for Kubernetes API server\n- discovery/consul/consul.go:123: HTTPClientConfig for Consul HTTP API\n- discovery/http/http.go:57: HTTPClientConfig for generic HTTP SD\n- discovery/nomad/nomad.go:69: HTTPClientConfig for Nomad SD\n- discovery/puppetdb/puppetdb.go:76: HTTPClientConfig for PuppetDB API\n- discovery/moby/docker.go:75: HTTPClientConfig for Docker daemon\n- discovery/moby/dockerswarm.go:55: HTTPClientConfig for Docker Swarm\n- discovery/xds/xds.go:52: HTTPClientConfig for xDS protocol\n- discovery/xds/client.go:68: HTTPClientConfig in HTTPResourceClientConfig\n- discovery/ionos/ionos.go:83: HTTPClientConfig for IONOS Cloud\n- discovery/vultr/vultr.go:72: HTTPClientConfig for Vultr API\n- discovery/openstack/openstack.go:65: TLSConfig for OpenStack API\n- discovery/triton/triton.go:69: TLSConfig for Triton Cloud\n- discovery/uyuni/uyuni.go:72: HTTPClientConfig for Uyuni platform\nAll plugins enforce TLS uniformly via either HTTPClientConfig embedding or direct TLSConfig usage.\n\n## TLS Validation and Verification\nThe promtool CLI validates TLS configuration across the stack:\n- cmd/promtool/main.go:607-622: CheckWebConfig validates web server TLS configuration files using web.Validate\n- cmd/promtool/main.go:760-779: checkTLSConfig validates TLS settings, ensuring cert/key pairs are properly matched\n- cmd/promtool/main.go:679: Validates TLS for scrape targets via checkTLSConfig\n- cmd/promtool/main.go:686: Validates TLS for Kubernetes service discovery plugins\n- cmd/prometheus/main.go:998: Validates web config via toolkit_web.Validate\n\nThis unified architecture ensures TLS is consistently enforced on all external interfaces: target scraping (scrape/scrape.go), remote storage (storage/remote/*), tracing exporters (tracing/tracing.go), service discovery (discovery/*), alertmanager communication (config/config.go), and the web server (web/web.go). The promtool validation tools verify configuration compliance across all these components."
}

